<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[835,1474,381,597]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,952,381,405]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is typically a shallow subtidal species (to about 
<quantity box="[946,1007,413,437]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
, i.e., Rahayu, 2000) but there are reports of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Estampador" authorityYear="1937" baseAuthorityName="Henderson" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[868,1019,445,469]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1019,445,469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. dearmatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<quantity box="[1092,1191,445,469]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" unit="m" value="37.5" valueMax="46.0" valueMin="29.0">29–46 m</quantity>
in the Admiralty Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson JR" box="[842,1029,477,501]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 221" refId="ref43230" refString="Henderson JR (1888) Report on the Anomura collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Scientific Results of the Exploratory Voyage of HMS Challenger (Zoology), 27: i-xi, 1 - 221." type="book chapter" year="1888">Henderson, 1888</bibRefCitation>
) or much deeper waters, e.g., 
<quantity box="[1353,1474,477,501]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" metricValueMax="9.15" metricValueMin="6.05" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" unit="m" value="760.0" valueMax="915.0" valueMin="605.0">605–915 m</quantity>
in Saya de Malha Bank (
<bibRefCitation author="Laurie RD" box="[1096,1238,509,533]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="121 - 167" refId="ref44414" refString="Laurie RD (1926) Reports of the Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905, under the leadership of Mr. J. Stanley Gardiner, M. A. Vol. 8, No. VI. - Anomura collected by Mr. J. Stanley Gardiner in the western Indian Ocean in H. M. S. Sealark. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 19: 121 - 167." type="journal article" year="1926">Laurie, 1926</bibRefCitation>
). The single specimen from Balicasag Island is also from relatively deep water (
<quantity box="[843,957,573,597]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" unit="m" value="275.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="50.0">50–500 m</quantity>
), and was collected via tangle net.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[835,1474,637,853]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation author="Cassidy PM" box="[835,1013,637,661]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="94 - 129" refId="ref41924" refString="Cassidy PM (2005) Some shallow-water hermit crabs of the genus Dardanus Paul'son 1875 (Decapoda: Paguroidea: Diogenidae) from the Visayan region of the Philippines with notes on their color and ecology. Philippine Scientist, 42: 94 - 129." type="journal article" year="2005">Cassidy (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, without further explanation, stated his opinion that 
<bibRefCitation author="Estampador EP" box="[978,1208,669,693]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="465 - 559" refId="ref42537" refString="Estampador EP (1937) A checklist of Philippine crustacean decapods. Philippine Journal of Science, 62 (4): 465 - 559." type="journal article" year="1937">Estampador’s (1937)</bibRefCitation>
report of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Estampador" authorityYear="1937" baseAuthorityName="Henderson" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1324,1474,669,693]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmatus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1474,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. dearmatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually refers to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1052,1207,702,725]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemmatus">
<emphasis box="[1052,1207,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. gemmatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Estampador EP" box="[1227,1473,701,725]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="465 - 559" refId="ref42537" refString="Estampador EP (1937) A checklist of Philippine crustacean decapods. Philippine Journal of Science, 62 (4): 465 - 559." type="journal article" year="1937">Estampador’s (1937)</bibRefCitation>
specimens could not be located for verification (
<bibRefCitation author="Asakura A &amp; Hirayama A" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="213 - 230" refId="ref41654" refString="Asakura A &amp; Hirayama A (2002) Dardanus jacquesi, a new species of hermit crab from the Indo-west Pacific, with the redescription of a little known species, Dardanus dearmatus (Henderson, 1888). Crustaceana, 75 (3 - 4): 213 - 230." type="journal article" year="2002">Asakura &amp; Hirayama, 2002: 229</bibRefCitation>
). Regardless of the identity of Estampador’s material, this report confirms the presence of 
<taxonomicName authority="in Philippine" authorityName="in Philippine" box="[835,1131,829,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmatus">
<emphasis box="[835,983,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. dearmatus</emphasis>
in Philippine
</taxonomicName>
waters.
</paragraph>
